%N A397157 Decimal expansion of the surface area of a canonical (dual-uniform) tetragonal trapezohedron with unit short edge length.
%C A397157 The tetragonal trapezohedron is the dual polyhedron of the square antiprism.
%H A397157 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A397157/b397157.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..10000</a>
%H A397157 David I. McCooey, <a href="https://dmccooey.com/polyhedra/TetragonalTrapezohedron.html">Tetragonal Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397157 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Square_antitegum">Square antitegum</a>.
%H A397157 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Trapezohedron.html">Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397157 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tetragonal_trapezohedron">Tetragonal trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397157 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_04">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 4</a>.
%F A397157 Equals 2*sqrt(22 + 16*sqrt(2)) = 2*sqrt(22 + A391952).
%F A397157 Equals the largest real root of x^4 - 176*x^2 - 448.
%e A397157 13.36075102649091665661381658268166687726987...
%t A397157 First[RealDigits[2*Sqrt[22 + Sqrt[512]], 10, 100]]
%t A397157 (* Alternative: *)
%t A397157 First[RealDigits[PolyhedronData[{"Trapezohedron", 4}, "SurfaceArea"], 10, 100]]
